      • buildUUID

        public static final java.lang.String buildUUID​(Person person,
                                               long timestamp,
                                               java.lang.String key)
        Construct a consistent UUID based on the given Person, timestamp, and a key. This method allows you to get the same UUID for a concept at a given point in time, when that concept does not map cleanly 1:1 to an object in the Synthea model. IMPORTANT: this is NOT random but attempts to minimize the likelihood of collisions.

      • buildUUID

        Construct a consistent UUID based on the given seed, timestamp, and a key. This method allows you to get the same UUID for a concept at a given point in time, when that concept does not map cleanly 1:1 to an object in the Synthea model. IMPORTANT: this is NOT random but attempts to minimize the likelihood of collisions.
